{{About|embedded motherboards|the European association|European Photovoltaic Industry Association|other uses|Epia (disambiguation){{!}}Epia}}
{{Computer case form factors}} [[File:VIA EPIA PD-10000.jpg|right|200px]] '''VIA EPIA''' (''[[VIA Technologies|VIA]] Embedded Platform Innovative Architecture'') is a series of [[mini-ITX]], em-ITX, [[nano-ITX]], [[pico-ITX]] and [[pico-ITXe]] [[motherboard]]s with integrated VIA [[Microprocessor|processor]]s. They are small in size and consume less power than computers of comparable capabilities.
There are several types of VIA EPIA motherboard: [[Nano-ITX]] versions, based on the [[VIA CoreFusion]] processor series, and [[Mini-ITX]] form factor featuring VIA CPUs and [[Northbridge (computing)|northbridges]] in separate packaging. They were originally built for industrial applications but came to have a wide range of applications in the consumer market, such as [[carputer]]s, [[Firewall (networking)|firewalls]], [[HTPC]]s, and Small File [[server (computing)|server]]s.{{Fact|date=February 2007}}.
